          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1689771379871-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped leek </strong>and cook for 3 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1689771384491-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
